Your data structure look like a **Map**, one mapping object to List.
**See Guava MultiMap here**
https://google.github.io/guava/releases/21.0/api/docs/com/google/common/collect/ListMultimap.html

If you don&#39;t want a dependency, you can do something like this:

    int parentIndex = parentList.indexOf(parentObject);
    if(parentIndex != -1){
       List&lt;Object&gt; children = parentList.get(parentIndex);
       if(children != null){
         children.remove(childIndex);
       }
     }

However, I recommend you use a [Map][1] to point to children.
   

    parentList.indexOf(parentObject);
does  a linear search which is O(n), as it may be a problem if your parent list is very large.


  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/Map.html

